# Resume & HANDOFF discipline

This project is formalized incrementally and sessions get reset by context compaction. Durable
state lives in files, not chat memory. Treat `HANDOFF.md` as the source of truth.

## On starting a session
- Read `HANDOFF.md` **first** (it has a "Resume Protocol" header listing what else to read).
- This repo's `arxiv.md` is the Part IV **paper** (bridges + dense proof notes) — keep it in
  sync when closing theorems; read relevant sections on resume.
- For dependency details, Grep the sibling inventories (`../scott1972/arxiv.md`,
  `../scott1980/arxiv.md`, `../scott1982/arxiv.md`) or read only the relevant Lean module —
  do **not** treat stale status prose in those files as blocking if Lean already ships the result.
- Sibling packages `scott1972`, `scott1980`, `scott1982` are **finished** sources; this package
  only builds the equivalence bridges.
- **Never** read, grep, or search `arxiv_with_code.md` (or other `arxiv_with_code.*` outputs).
  That file is **auto-generated** for the PDF pipeline; it is listed in `.cursorignore` when present.

## On finishing a work item (bridge theorem / lemma module)
After the item builds green, do all of the following before ending the turn:
1. `lake build ScottModels` is green and zero `sorry`; run an axiom audit
   (`#print axioms <name>`) and confirm `⊆ {propext, Quot.sound}` unless choice is unavoidable
   (classical frontier: document in the proof note).
2. Append a dated checkpoint to `HANDOFF.md` and update its "Resume Protocol" / status lines.
3. Update the corresponding section / catalog row in `arxiv.md` with a dense proof note
   (not status-only). In Markdown tables, **escape literal `|` as `\|`**.
4. Wire any new module into `ScottModels.lean`.

## Context-cost hygiene
- Filter shell output (`| grep -vE 'LEAN_PATH|trace:' | tail`) so builds don't dump thousands of lines.
- Prefer appending to the end of `HANDOFF.md` over rewriting its middle (keeps the prompt cache warm).
- Batch independent tool calls in one turn.

## Choice discipline
Data constructions must stay choice-free (`[propext, Quot.sound]`). `Classical.choice` is allowed
only for `Prop`-level results where it is genuinely unavoidable (esp. 1972 topology / classical
frontier), and must be called out in notes.
